   {:e #blake3 "eadc54bed0cd0c1d3e232a908bc668f4737782e3b6430d4305e9d5a6824ca374" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: The agent needs to know which observations come from which agents, and which observations agree. The current store has 226 audit observations from 4 independent agents but cannot answer 'which findings do multiple agents agree on?' RATIONALE: This is a composable primitive — a pure function over datoms that any consumer (seed, status, query) can use. It does NOT depend on the concept engine or embeddings. It operates at the OBSERVATION entity level, grouping by creating agent (datom.tx.agent) and computing agreement via textual similarity of :exploration/body titles (first 80 chars). This avoids the HashEmbedder concept-collapse problem entirely. APPROACH: (1) New types: AgentObservationGroup { agent: AgentId, agent_name: String, observations: Vec<EntityId> }. AgreementCluster { topic: String, agents: Vec<AgentId>, observation_ids: Vec<EntityId>, confidence_range: (f64,f64,f64), agreement_score: f64 }. (2) New fn agent_observation_groups(store: &Store) -> Vec<AgentObservationGroup>: iterate observations, extract datom.tx.agent from first datom per entity, group into HashMap<AgentId, Vec<EntityId>>. O(observations). (3) New fn find_agreement_clusters(store: &Store, similarity_threshold: f64) -> Vec<AgreementCluster>: for each pair of observations from DIFFERENT agents, compute title similarity (Jaccard over word tokens of first 80 chars of :exploration/body). If similarity > threshold (default 0.4), they agree on the same topic. Agglomerative merge of agreement pairs into clusters. Score = |distinct_agents| / |total_agents|. (4) New fn format_agreement_summary(clusters: &[AgreementCluster]) -> Vec<String>: format for braid status display. KEY DESIGN: This is a UNIX-STYLE PRIMITIVE. It takes a store, returns data. It does not modify the seed or guidance or status — those consume it as they choose. The only coupling is the datom schema. ALGEBRAIC PROPERTY: agreement_score is monotonically non-decreasing as confirming agents are added (adding an agent never reduces the score). This makes it a join-semilattice over agent sets — consistent with the store's CRDT algebra. ACCEPTANCE: (A) Given 3 agents observing same finding, cluster has agreement_score=3/3. (B) Given 3 agents observing 3 different findings, no cluster exceeds agreement_score=1/3. (C) O(observations^2) for pairwise comparison — acceptable for N<1000. (D) format_agreement_summary produces human-readable output consumable by braid status. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/concept.rs (collocated with observation logic). EFFORT: 4h." :op :assert}
